title: Use types-publisher as tester
body:
This switches us to using `types-publisher` rather than `definition-tester` to test packages.
Due to the new organization in `types-2.0`, the new tester is a simple script that runs `tsc` in every directory. It also runs through much of the types-publishing machinery before that, so we won't have as many surprises during publishing.
Travis logs of this PR should show the new tester running. However, it won't test any packages. I created a sample at PR with changes andy-ms/DefinitelyTyped#1 and that seems to work.

title: Use only 1 process for running tests (stop travis from crashing)
body:
By default the tester uses `os.cpus().length` processes. On travis, this value is `32`. But when we try to launch 32 processes, the travis job is killed.
I suspect that Travis may be giving the number of CPUs available on the machine running the virtualized container, but more than one process runs on that container. More info [here](https://theza.ch/2014/09/17/cpu-resources-in-docker-mesos-and-marathon/).
